reviews.review_text:
at last...! After downloading the majority of this show elsewhere & burning to disc, I discover this recording!  The best version of this show posted here.  Just canned what I had and am downloading this to replace it...

A hit 'n miss stand, and the two shows each reflected that ~ but the energy is more fun on this night and though the first set here can't match the next night's crazy setlist, it's played with brighter energy.

This stand (and its roadtrip) is classic more for the friends it forged than for the brilliance of its performance.  But it was summer at Alpine, and it sure was a blast.  Heat and ganja drought notwithstanding (drought of '86 in full swing, imagine if you can two nights' GD parking lot camping scene without herb, no joke). 

Some real moments here, though, standout versions of Ramble On Rose, China Doll, and both encore songs, Saturday Night & Baby Blue.  Fastest Touch of Grey ever?  A sour chord in the 2nd verse of Looks Like Rain leads to the band seriously stepping up to make up for it ~ Jerry's lead shimmers, and Bob's rap does, too.  And plenty of space jams in the second set, even if they didn't always feel cohesive.

Summer '86~ This sweet FOB AUD is my favorite pull from this show.  I like the raucous Bucket to open and the rippin' Ramble on Rose that follows, and the Row Jimmy is well played, too!  I also like the song selection in the second set - ok, another tune, maybe a Terrapin, would have been nice - but i don't like the lightning-fast pace of the tunes played post-China Doll.  The Saturday Night > Baby Blue encore is a teriffic topper~
